  "cooking_instructions": [
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Boil a full kettle</p><p>Peel and finely chop (or grate) the <strong>garlic</strong></p><p>Chop the <strong>coriander</strong> and <strong>parsley </strong>roughly, including the stalks</p>",
      "order": 1,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-1-1630491700926-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-1-1630491700926-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-1-1630491700926-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-1-1630491700926-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-1-1630491700926-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Add <strong>half</strong> the <strong>chopped garlic</strong> to a <strong>food processor</strong> with the <strong>chopped coriander & parsley</strong></p><p>Add<strong> half</strong> the <strong>ground</strong> <strong>cumin</strong> (you’ll use the rest later), the juice of 1/2 <span class=\"text-danger\">[1] </span><strong>lemon</strong>, 2 tbsp <span class=\"text-danger\">[4 tbsp]</span> <strong>olive</strong> <strong>oil</strong> and a pinch of <strong>salt</strong> and blitz well until you’re left with a <strong>green</strong> <strong>sauce</strong> – this is your <strong>chermoula</strong></p>",
      "order": 2,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-2-1630491719589-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-2-1630491719589-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-2-1630491719589-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-2-1630491719589-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-2-1630491719589-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Cut the <strong>basa fillets</strong> into bite-sized pieces and add them to a bowl with <strong>half</strong> the <strong>chermoula</strong> (save the rest for later!)</p><p>Give them a good mix up until they are fully coated and set aside to marinate</p><p>Meanwhile, peel and finely slice the <strong>brown onion<span class=\"text-danger\">[s]</span></strong></p><p>Deseed the <strong>red pepper<span class=\"text-danger\">[s]</span></strong> (scrape the seeds and pith out with a teaspoon) and cut into thin strips</p>",
      "order": 3,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-3-1630491741747-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-3-1630491741747-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-3-1630491741747-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-3-1630491741747-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-3-1630491741747-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Heat a large, wide-based pan (preferably non-stick) with a matching lid with a drizzle of <strong>olive oil</strong> over a medium-high heat</p><p>Once hot, add the <strong>pepper strips</strong> and cook for 4-5 min or until starting to char slightly</p><p>Once charred, reduce the heat to medium and add the <strong>sliced onion </strong>and<strong> remaining chopped garlic</strong> with a pinch of <strong>salt</strong> and cook for 3-4 min further or until slightly softened</p>",
      "order": 4,
      "media": {
        "images": [
